==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Upstroke
<hw>Up"stroke`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An upward stroke,
especially the stroke, or line, made by a writing instrument when moving
upward, or from the body of the writer, or a line corresponding to the
part of a letter thus made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some <qex>upstroke</qex> of an Alpha and Omega.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upsun</ent>⟦br⟧
